This paper is about deep learning-based 3D human pose estimation for videos, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that utilizes matrix factorization, which falls under the category of ML algorithms. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also evaluates its approach on multiple benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper's approach can be applied to robotics (RO) applications, such as human-robot interaction, which is another possible sub-category.
